# WKFindResult

**Class**

An object that contains the results of searching the web view’s contents.

## Declaration

```swift
@MainActor class WKFindResult
```

## Overview

When you perform a search using the methods of [doc://com.apple.webkit/documentation/WebKit/WKWebView], the web view creates a [doc://com.apple.webkit/documentation/WebKit/WKFindResult] object and delivers it to your completion handler. You don’t create instances of this class directly. Use the objects that the web view provides to determine whether it found a match for the content.

## Getting the Search Result

- **matchFound**: A Boolean value that indicates whether the web view found a match during the search.

## Page-level search

- **WKFindConfiguration**: The configuration parameters to use when searching the contents of the web view.

## Inherits From

- NSObject

## Conforms To

- CVarArg
- CustomDebugStringConvertible
- CustomStringConvertible
- Equatable

- NSCopying

- Sendable
